ESVP – Explorer, Shopper, Vacationer, Prisoner

This is a short activity to measure participants’ engagement for the meeting at hand

Running the activity
 
1. Ask each participant to report anonymously his or her attitude toward the retrospective as an Explorer, Shopper, Vacationer or Prisoner.
– Explorers – Are eager to discover new ideas and insights. They want to learn everything they can about the iteration/release/project.
– Shoppers – Will look over all the available information, and will be happy to go home with one useful new idea.
– Vacationers – Aren’t interested in the work of the retrospective, but are happy to be away from the daily grind.
– Prisoners – Feel that they’ve been forced to attend and would rather be doing something else.
2. Collect the results and create a histogram to show the data.
3. Acknowledge the results and guide a discussion about what the results mean for the group.

索者（Explorer）, 采购者（Shopper）, 度假者（Vacationer）与囚徒（Prisoner）
这是个小的活动，用来衡量参与者对手头会议的参与态度。
如何开展
1．请每位参与者匿名公布他或她对回顾会议的态度，是探索者、采购者、度假者还是囚徒。
－探索者——渴望发现新的主意和洞察。对于迭代／版本发布／项目，他们想学会所有可以学到的东西。
－采购者——将会查看所有能够得到的信息，还会很乐意把个有用的新主意带回家。
－采购者——对回顾工作不感兴趣，但是很高兴能远离日常的工作。
－囚徒——觉得他们是被迫出席的，所以宁愿去做点儿其它的事儿。
2.收集结果并且创建直方图来显示数据。
3.确认结果，并引导大家讨论这些结果对团队有什么意义。

ESVP－探
